% Handwritten A0 — Milestone 1 corpus (token_bucket)
% Each requirement line maps to story ## Covers R1–R4 (see stories/).

<requirements>
When a request is allowed, return True and decrement tokens.
When the bucket is empty, reject the request and return False.
Refill tokens at a steady rate over time.
Duplicate requests within a short window should be handled safely.
</requirements>

<vocabulary>
- duplicate: returns an observable outcome defined by this prompt's rules
</vocabulary>

<contract_rules>
R1 - Requirement 1
When When a request is allowed, return True and decrement tokens
The module MUST satisfy this requirement with an observable outcome.
R2 - Requirement 2
When When the bucket is empty, reject the request and return False
The module MUST satisfy this requirement with an observable outcome.
R3 - Requirement 3
When Refill tokens at a steady rate over time
The module MUST satisfy this requirement with an observable outcome.
R4 - Requirement 4
When Duplicate requests within a short window should be handled safely
The module MUST satisfy this requirement with an observable outcome.
</contract_rules>

<coverage>
- R1: story__token_bucket.md
- R2: story__token_bucket.md
- R3: story__token_bucket.md
- R4: story__token_bucket.md
</coverage>
